Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to generate representations of unstructured pixel data through emergent communication between speaker and listener agents. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and specifically natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of population-based approaches and analysis of communication dynamics suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the post-hoc analysis of the factors induced by population-based learning suggests a potential interest in systems and control (cs.SD).
